I can't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  believe</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> half the stuff posted here... you druids seem SO obsessed with the shaman's ability to slow, as a much better healer than you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  NEWS FLASH: THE FOLLOWING CLASSES CAN ALSO SLOW</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Chances are, you probably will have the opportunity to group with one, too!<br>
<br>
Enchanter - 70% at level 58<br>
Bard - not exactly sure, probably like 40% with an instrument<br>
Ranger - Epic procs, 40% slow<br>
Necro -50% undead slow, perfect in howling stones. Hey they can also heal well too! bonus!<br>
Beastlord - 30% spell, 55% epic.<br>
<br>
If you're going to bitch about not being able to heal in groups, it's your own nimrodic fault for including a class that makes your job eaier <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Secondly... you will whine and whine about torpor, the disadvantages of which have already been explained one hundred times over. You're comparing your STORE BOUGHT SPELL to our extremely rare, balanced due to limitations and inability to cast it out of group, heal over time, which is often highly inferior to a direct heal, ESPECIALLY when you are trying to get someone out of low HP agro.<br>
<br>
For God's sake...that heal you guys suggested on the other page... 2500hp for 350 mana....you want a spell that heals more than twice the health of torpor, for 150 more mana, in a direct heal, with no penalties.... if so, this spell had better drop off Diablo Xi Va or something...  The fact that you can buy an entire druid spellbook several times over (Minus a couple gems they share with others like Sol Levi/EB and RGC)... for the price that this one spell fetches on most servers... and guess what? we have 4 other spells that are the same price and rarity! whoop-de-frickin'-do!<br>
<br>
Essentially, you are only thinking of yourselves, me me me, it's my job to heal in the group, I'm all by myself. Instead, how about using that brain and finding a way to work with other classes to solve your limitations? You might be pleasantly surprised.<br>
<br>
Okay I'm done ranting... again think of it this way... you clicked your character, you saw LOW DIFFICULTY... and you assumed by freeloading your way through the game you get to see the best ending. How quaint.<br>
<br>
