Author: Bamana DeMoro<br>
Subject: Re: Dropped Spells<br>
<br>
I totally agree that dropped spells were poorly thought out.<br>
<br>
Most of the population will never see the mobs needed to attain some of the rarer spells. When will VI realize that spells aren't like our weapons, they're like our disciplines, they are our life's blood. <br>
<br>
A melee with poor weapons is still wanted in groups because they can still deal/take damage. A caster without key/rare spells is passed up in favor of those who have those spells because they simply cannot contribute as much.<br>
<br>
This is an inherant imbalance.<br>
<br>
VI, big, sweeping changes aren't really needed to Balance casters. Give us all our spells, (the ones all the ubers already have anyhow) and we will be well on our way to being competitive.<br>
<br>
I have no problem with Ancient spells dropping off uber mobs, but don't make it harder for us to get to the point where we can kill uber mobs. <br>
<br>
Many casters are stuck in lower &quot;tier&quot; guilds and cannot get the spells we need, this leads to us not getting into the groups we need, wich further contributes to us being left out. <br>
<br>
Please, when balancing casters don't forget the plight of those 99% of us who would be a lot closer to being &quot;balanced&quot; if we had a full spell book (minus ancient spells, of course). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udyrk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dyrk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>First Post!</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 5:38:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=710.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moved reply - Originally on update on balance thread</span><hr size=1> Wait a second...<br>
<br>
&quot;When will VI realize that spells aren't like our weapons, they're like our disciplines, they are our life's blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
And most of those spells you can purchase for a pittance from a vendor. At least up until the high end ones. This is where your analogy to a melee's gear actually is a good one. How many melee's do you know who have EVER used a single piece of gear that was purchased at a merchant? How many 10's of K PP does a melee need to shell out for continual upgrades until he can't even buy the high end ones because they become NO DROP? How many in the high end game have few items that aren't even NO DROP?  <br>
<br>
A warrior with poor weapons CANNOT hold agro and thus can't fulfill his role as a main tank. 5000  hp? Defensive Discipline? Who cares?  If you can't keep the mobs attention -- through use of high end/high taunt weapons -- it becomes useless. Other melee's with poor weapons have a lower DPS and are therefore less valuable. Sounds like both casters and melees are in somewhat of the same boat here.<br>
<br>
People have spoken out against the homogenization of all the classes. What about the homogenization within a single class? Shouldn't there be something to distinguish the truly dedicated and excellent players at the top of the their servers from others? <br>
<br>
-Duurk<br>
